Title: Organza Embroidery Fabric
desc: Organza is a light sheer fabric that was originally made from silk. The modernized version of the fabric however, can be created not only with silk but also polyester or nylon, or even a blend of the three. While the look and feel is similar to silk, it is a lot thinner and is made of a plain weave. Organza is also known for being a lightweight material as well as being a crisp and stiff fabric. Our organza embroideries range in various different colours of the base fabric, having various patters and designs with work of sequins , silk and viscose thread work and zari.

Coffee Georgette Printed Fabric

Georgette Fabric is originally named after the French dressmaker Georgette de la Plante. Georgette Fabric refers to a thin, semi-transparent fabric with a dry hand and grainy surface due to the high twist per inch of the warp and weft threads. With so much twist in the yarns, this material has a natural bounce that makes anything that is created come alive. Perfect for lightweight flowing scarves and fanciful attire, this material has a personality all its own.

Chanderi Embroidery Fabric
desc: A beautiful blend of Cotton, Silk thread and zari results to Chanderi fabric. Chanderi fabric comes from a small town, Chanderi town in Madhya Pradesh. The fabric is a result of traditional methods of hand weaving that have been developed over the centuries and passed down through generations. Create your own designs by selecting our Chanderi embroideries in different shades of pastels and earthy colours, with a work of different embroidered coloured threads, patterns and designs.
